# SigTekX - StreamingExecutor Pipeline Sequence
# Layout: elk - complex sequence diagram with multiple actors and parallel flows
# Render: See docs/diagrams/README.md for rendering instructions
#
# This diagram shows the complete execution flow for StreamingExecutor (low-latency streaming mode).
# The sequence illustrates ring buffer accumulation, batched frame processing (Optimization 3.1),
# zero-copy peek_frame_at_offset DMA, and 3-stream asynchronous execution.
#
# UPDATED: 2026-03-10 — Batched frame processing (Optimization 3.1)

# Import shared styles
...@common/styles

direction: down

# ==============================================================================
# Streaming Executor Pipeline (Continuous Streaming Mode)
# ==============================================================================
streaming_mode: Streaming Executor Pipeline {
  class: streaming-green

  description: |md
    **Streaming Mode: Ring Buffer Accumulation + Batched Frame Processing**
    - Supports arbitrary input chunk sizes
    - Per-channel independent processing
    - Ring buffer capacity: 3× NFFT per channel
    - **Batched path (Opt 3.1)**: N frames in 1 GPU submission (1 sync vs N)
    - **Dispatch**: N=0 → no-op, N=1 → process_one_batch, N≥2 → process_batched_frames
    - Ideal for real-time continuous streaming
  |

  # Actor definitions
  Client: {shape: rectangle}
  StreamingExecutor: {shape: rectangle}
  Impl: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "StreamingExecutor::Impl"
  }
  RingBuffer: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "RingBuffer[ch]\n(pinned)"
  }
  Stream0: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "Stream[0]\nH2D"
  }
  Stream1: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "Stream[1]\nCompute"
  }
  Stream2: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "Stream[2]\nD2H"
  }
  Kernels: {
    shape: rectangle
    label: "Direct Kernel Launches\n(bypass stages for N≥2)"
  }
  WindowStage: {shape: rectangle}
  FFTStage: {shape: rectangle}
  MagnitudeStage: {shape: rectangle}

  # Sequence flow
  Client -> StreamingExecutor: "1: submit(input, output, num_samples)"
  StreamingExecutor -> Impl: "2: submit_impl(input, output, num_samples)"

  # Ring Buffer Accumulation
  Impl -> RingBuffer: "3: for each channel:\npush(input_chunk[ch], num_samples)"
  RingBuffer -> RingBuffer: "4: Lock-free push\nAtomic write_pos update"
  RingBuffer -> Impl: "5: push complete"

  # Frame Count + Dispatch (Optimization 3.1)
  Impl -> Impl: "6: N = count_available_frames()\n(min available across channels, clamped to max_frames)"

  # ====== BATCHED PATH (N ≥ 2) ======
  # Zero-copy H2D: peek all N frames from ring buffers
  Impl -> RingBuffer: "7: for frame_i in 0..N-1, for each ch:\npeek_frame_at_offset(nfft, frame_i × hop_size)"
  RingBuffer -> RingBuffer: "8: Returns FrameView{first, second}\n(ptrs at staggered offsets into pinned ring buf)"

  # Host to Device Transfer (all N frames in one shot)
  RingBuffer -> Stream0: "9: cudaMemcpyAsync × (N × channels)\n(DMA all frames to d_input)"
  Stream0 -> Stream0: "10: record event_h2d_done\nLayout: [ch0_f0|ch1_f0|ch0_f1|ch1_f1|...]"

  # Compute Pipeline (3 kernel launches for all N frames)
  Stream1 -> Stream0: "11: wait(event_h2d_done)"

  Stream1 -> Kernels: "12: launch_apply_window(d_input, d_input, d_window)\nbatch = N × channels, stride = nfft"
  Kernels -> Kernels: "13: apply_window_kernel<<<>>>\n(in-place, all N×channels blocks)"

  Stream1 -> Kernels: "14: batched_fft_plan.exec_r2c(d_input, d_intermediate)\nbatch = N × channels (lazy cached plan)"
  Kernels -> Kernels: "15: cuFFT R2C\n(all N×channels transforms)"

  Stream1 -> Kernels: "16: launch_magnitude(d_intermediate, d_output)\nbatch = N × channels, stride = output_bins"
  Kernels -> Kernels: "17: magnitude_kernel<<<>>>\n(all N×channels blocks)"

  Stream1 -> Stream1: "18: record event_compute_done"

  # Device to Host Transfer (LAST FRAME ONLY)
  Stream2 -> Stream1: "19: wait(event_compute_done)"
  Stream2 -> Stream2: "20: cudaMemcpyAsync(output, d_output + last_frame_offset)\n(Only last frame: channels × output_bins floats)"

  # Single synchronization point (1 sync instead of N)
  Impl -> Stream2: "21: cudaStreamSynchronize()\n(SINGLE sync for all N frames)"
  Stream2 -> Impl: "22: D2H complete"

  # Advance ring buffers by total consumed
  Impl -> RingBuffer: "23: advance(N × hop_size)\n(Bulk advance — safe after sync)"

  Impl -> Impl: "24: frame_counter++, update_stats()\n(frames_processed += N)"

  Impl -> StreamingExecutor: "25: submit complete"
  StreamingExecutor -> Client: "26: return (last frame in output)"

  # ====== SINGLE-FRAME PATH (N = 1) ======
  single_frame_note: {
    class: note-gold
    label: |md
      **N=1 Fallback**: Uses existing `process_one_batch()` path
      (identical to pre-optimization behavior — zero overhead)

      **N=0**: No frames available, no processing
    |
  }

  performance_stream_note: {
    class: note-gold
    label: |md
      **Optimization 3.1: Batched Frame Processing**
      - **Before**: [H2D→W→FFT→Mag→D2H→SYNC] × N  (N syncs, 3N kernel launches)
      - **After**: [H2D_all→W_all→FFT_all→Mag_all→D2H_last→SYNC]  (1 sync, 3 launches)
      - **Expected**: 2-6× latency reduction for high overlap configs

      **Key design decisions**:
      - Bypass stages → call kernel wrappers directly (preserves stage interface)
      - Lazy cuFFT plan cache (keyed by N×channels)
      - D2H last frame only (API contract: one output per submit)
      - peek_frame_at_offset() for zero-copy staggered DMA
    |
  }
}

# ==============================================================================
# Comparison Note
# ==============================================================================
comparison: |md
  # Batch vs Streaming Mode Comparison

  ## Batch Executor (High-Throughput - see 06_cpp_seq_batch.d2)
  - **Direct pipeline**: H2D → Compute → D2H
  - **Fixed input size**: Must provide complete frames
  - **Lower latency**: ~405 µs (Python end-to-end)
  - **Use case**: Offline batch processing, file analysis

  ## Streaming Executor (Low-Latency Real-Time - THIS DIAGRAM)
  - **Ring buffer accumulation**: Flexible chunk sizes
  - **Batched frame processing** (Optimization 3.1): 1 sync per submit, not N
  - **Zero-copy H2D**: peek_frame_at_offset() DMA from pinned ring buffer
  - **Dispatch**: N=1 → single-frame path, N≥2 → batched path
  - **Use case**: Real-time streaming, continuous monitoring

  Both modes use the same 3-stream asynchronous pipeline for parallel H2D/Compute/D2H.
|

comparison.class: core-blue
